<br>
We have been investigating a strange bout of happenings in our Knights newly inherited Lordship.  Our present party consists of an 8th level Paladin (our lord), 10th level sorcerer, 10th level wizard, 10th level bard, 8th level thief, 10th level warrior (half orc, very nasty *grin) 9th lvl cleric, 10th level bard, and myself.. 10th level monk.<br>
<br>
Well, as the story unfolds we discover a strange house.. actually it happens that the bard and I stumbled upon this home while a party was in session... the Lady of the home had a picture of our lord hanging over her mantle.  Once we returned to the castle and inquired to the lord about this lady, we discovered he had no idea who this lady was.... as we prepare to leave the castle in order to return to the house with our lord, we find a body in the courtyard.  It has obviously been the sacrifice for some sort of ritual, as it was laid out on the ground, with his intrails in a circle around his body and all his other body organs missing.  The cleric casts a spell to be able to speak with this person and we find out he was killed because he betrayed the "Lady in Waiting" to our lord, somehow.  Well, we are off to find out more about this, and this house seems like the perfect place to start. <br>
<br>
We get there and find the place completely deserted and dust covered.  And the picture on the mantle is no longer the same painting of our lord.  It is now a painting of a throne room, and inside it is a glass coffin (empty).. the coffin of the "Lady in Waiting"<br>
<br>
. . . . <br>
<br>
Well, we decide to get out of town for a while and go investigate some other things that may help us in this endeavor.  As we leave a magical storm begins brewing..and hail begins to fall... hail that is covered in fire!!!  I find a place for us to take shelter (not before catching on fire a few times =P)<br>
<br>
The party is gathered in this cellar, when we hear a scraping at the door.  As we are missing a few party members, the bard asks me to open the door.  BOY, do I open the door... I completely DESTROY the door... and in creeps a shadow...  a shadow that NO ONE ELSE CAN SEEM TO SEE!!!!  Battle between the shadow and myself ensues, and the DM tells me, make a fortitude save.   Errr, does a 1 save????  haha nope... guess what?  Zamori, you just lost a level!   <br>
<br>
gah!!!  finally my party is aware of the presence of this thing and begin to help me out a little!  Now our dear sweet cleric decides to cast flash of light.  Lovely.  Make a saving throw, Zam.  Does a 4 save?  You are now blind for 5 rounds.  <br>
<br>
Make a fortitude save, Zam...  Does a 7 save?  Zamori, you have lost another level.  son of a...........<br>
<br>
=)  <br>
